comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T10:52:12.165Z",codex,"PR #17 finishing audit (2026-07-10): aligned manifest/runtime/package version at 2026.7.6 and added a regression invariant; made spawn failures expose result.error and remain expected errors; string-normalized positional plan/search/history inputs; kept afterCommand hints behind PM_TS_STARTER_VERBOSE; corrected --id precedence docs. Real CLI testing found mocked-contract gaps and fixed them: search keywords, history item id, and plan show id are positional in pm 2026.7.10. Verified npm ci/build/typecheck and 9/9 tests; installed local build into /tmp/fx-pm-ts-starter; timeout 20 pm --help returned 0; created two tasks plus a plan; context-demo, search-demo (1 hit), history-compact-demo (dry_run true), plan-demo (1 pending step), info/setup all succeeded. Blank search produced structured PmCliError guidance and exit 2 without a stack trace. Compared no-flag pm hello against origin/main: stdout and stderr identical. pm-changelog full and changelog:check passed. Bot decisions: Greptile version mismatch valid; Gemini/Cubic argument/spawn/default-noise/precedence findings valid; Cubic mock-dedup is maintainability-only and left unchanged to avoid unrelated churn; Hound dist warnings are false positives from parsing generated modern ESM as pre-ES6."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-07T07:41:58.063Z",codex-5.3-full-cycle,"Hardening pass complete: release:check succeeded after dependency bump and changelog regeneration."
  "2026-06-07T08:00:45.261Z",codex-5.3-full-cycle,"Security gate: high-confidence token/key regex scan over tracked files and git history found no actionable secrets. Binary-history false positives were traced to embedded wasm base64 blobs, not credentials."
